thread.title: 'Best atmosphere in college football': Rutgers vs. Ohio State?
thread.title_full: 'Best atmosphere in college football': Rutgers vs. Ohio State?

author: app.com
title: 'Best atmosphere in college football': Rutgers vs. Ohio State?
text:
MORE PISCATAWAY - ESPN's "College Gameday" show is headed to James Madison, but perhaps it is missing the boat on Ohio State at Rutgers.
Rutgers is hosting the top-ranked defending national champions at 8 p.m. Saturday at High Point Solutions Stadium. It will be the first ABC national television broadcast in Rutgers football history .
"Saturday night will be the best atmosphere in all of college football," Rutgers coach Kyle Flood said Tuesday on the weekly Big Ten teleconference.
"Anybody who has ever been to a primetime night game at High Point Solutions Stadium will tell you that. The country got a little glimpse of that a couple weeks ago when we played Michigan State, and I think it will be amped up even a little bit higher this week with the No. 1 team in the country coming to town."
